[{"id":"VR598281","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR598278.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The first three stanzas (lines 1-15) develop the poem’s overall argument mainly by</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR598281_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><p class=\"introduction passage-intro\">Read the following poem carefully before you choose your answers.</p><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">Mercedes de Acosta’s poem “Life and Youth” was published in 1921.</span></p></div></div><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"poetry style:1\"><div class=\"title\"><p class=\"title_line passage-title\">Life and Youth</p></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Through the archways of Life I tread,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Nor do I walk with much less dread,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Because I know</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>That where I go,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">5</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Millions have walked before me.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I do not feel less pain because ’tis said,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>That saints and martyrs and soldiers have bled</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>For what they gave.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I am not brave</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">10</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Because of this.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I weep not less,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Because in distress</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Others, perhaps being stronger, have not wept as much;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>For Stoics,<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">1</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">members of a school of philosophy who hold the belief that one should be free from passion and unmoved by joy or grief</span></span> and tearless people, and because of such</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">15</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Restraint, I hold not back my tears.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I borrow not my courage from the crowd.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>My heart is heavy and my head is bowed—</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>But were I to raise my head high,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And cast my eyes up to the sky,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">20</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>A star might guide me.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I cannot be what has been,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I cannot see what’s been seen.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I shape my course,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And gather force,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">25</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>From what’s to come.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The future is my golden star,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>My inspiration—and from afar,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I see the deeds that may be done,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I watch a race that may be run,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">30</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And hold my breath in ecstasy.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Away! Black shadows of the past,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Stale traditions that hold us fast.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Because they were,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Must we not stir</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">35</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>From off their worn out path?</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I take up the spade of Youth and of Life,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And fling new pebbles on the path, where strife</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Has worn the old ones out.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I dig and put to rout,<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">2</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">“Put to rout” is an expression meaning force out.</span></span></span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">40</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Old fancies and old doubt.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Across the world I hear a clear, new note;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The locks are shattered and the chains are smote,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And a moonbeam has fallen across life’s shoulder.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I raise my sword, and like a pioneer soldier,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">45</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I sharpen it on the Shield of Hope.</span><br/></div><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\"></span></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">presenting a series of comparable examples to establish the speaker’s predicament</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">juxtaposing several metaphors to convey the complexity of the speaker’s despair</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">referencing an image repeatedly to emphasize the speaker’s determination</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">using flashback to highlight the gradual development of the speaker’s point of view</p>"],"answer":0}]